
Abstraction is a process of hiding the implementation details and showing only the functionality to the user.

Abstract method :
    When we require only method declaration in parent class. This can be done by abstract method.
    eg : to declare an abstract method, this form is used : abstract void methodName();

    Some Benefits :
    1. Helps to increase the security of code.
    2. Helps to to make code more rigid.
    3. Helps to hide details from the user.
    4. It provides flexibility.
    5. It provides scalability.
    6. focuses more  on functionality and hide implementation because requirement is not their.
    7. with abstract method and abstract class we achieve abstraction in JAVA.


Abstract method is the method without body. and here abstract keyword is mandatory.
An abstract class is mean to be extended. abstract class must be extended by the child class